hint.text:
The cube of an integer with a number 'x' in the unit's place will always have a number 'y' in the unit's place of its cube number.
For example, \(8^3=512\) and \(18^3=5832\).
Notice that \(8\) is in the unit's place of the given integer and \(2\) is in the unit's place of the square number.

solution.text:
\(_{j}_^3\)
\(=_{j}_ \times _{j}_ \times _{j}_\)
\(=_{{j**3}}_\)
Therefore, \(6\) lies in the one's digit of the cube of \(_{j}_\).
